    Derivations for Max Share Identification Method

    Calculate the forecast error variance for a VAR out to a specified horizon

    fev.Rd

    Calculate the forecast error variance for a VAR out to a specified horizon

    Usage

    fev(var, n_ahead = 20)

    Arguments

    var

    vars::VAR or svars object

    n_ahead

    number of steps out to calculate fev

    Value

    forecast error variance

    Examples

    x <- svars::USA
v <- vars::VAR(x, p = 2)
mvar <- id_fevdtd(v, "pi", 4:10)
fev(mvar)
